The paper presents a theoretical model of social learning with coordination motives, which involves decision-making and game theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Game Theory and Decision Science). The paper also involves statistical inference and learning, which suggests the category cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper uses mathematical analysis to study the model, which suggests the category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves discrete time and community structures, which suggests the category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the issue of equilibrium selection, which suggests the category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
